## 💡 License Quick Reference

### 🟢 Low Risk (Permissive)

**MIT** - Most permissive
- ✅ Commercial use
- ✅ Modification
- ✅ Distribution
- ✅ Private use
- ⚠️ Must include copyright notice

**Apache-2.0** - Includes patent grant
- ✅ Same as MIT
- ✅ **Plus:** Patent protection
- ⚠️ Must state changes

**BSD-3-Clause** - Similar to MIT
- ✅ Same as MIT
- ⚠️ Cannot use author's name for endorsement

**ISC** - Functionally identical to MIT
- ✅ Same as MIT
- Simpler legal wording

---

### 🟡 Medium Risk (Weak Copyleft)

**MPL-2.0** (Mozilla)
- ✅ Commercial use
- ✅ Can mix with proprietary
- ⚠️ File-level copyleft (modified MPL files must be open)

**LGPL** (Lesser GPL)
- ✅ Can link to proprietary
- ⚠️ Modified LGPL code must be open
- Complex compliance requirements

**EPL** (Eclipse)
- ✅ Commercial use
- ⚠️ Module-level copyleft
- Patent retaliation clause

---

### 🔴 High Risk (Strong Copyleft)

**GPL-2.0/3.0** (GNU General Public)
- ❌ **Forces entire project open-source**
- ❌ Cannot use in proprietary software
- ⚠️ Derivative works must use GPL

**AGPL** (Affero GPL)
- ❌ **Strictest copyleft**
- ❌ Network use = distribution (must open source)
- ⚠️ SaaS applications affected

**Avoid in commercial projects!**

